# =============================================================================
# Psst Cloud Functions - Environment Variables Template
# =============================================================================
#
# This file documents all required environment variables for Psst Cloud Functions.
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your actual API keys.
#
# IMPORTANT: Never commit `.env` to version control! It's already in .gitignore.
#
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OpenAI Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used for:
# - AI chat completions (GPT-4)
# - Text embeddings generation (text-embedding-3-small)
# - Function calling capabilities
#
# Where to get it:
# 1. Sign up at https://platform.openai.com/
# 2. Navigate to API Keys section
# 3. Create a new secret key
#
# Format: sk-proj-... or sk-...
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-api-key-here

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Pinecone Configuration
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used for:
# - Vector storage (message embeddings)
# - Semantic search (RAG - Retrieval Augmented Generation)
# - Similarity queries for AI conversation context
#
# Where to get it:
# 1. Sign up at https://www.pinecone.io/
# 2. Create a serverless index (1536 dimensions, cosine metric)
# 3. Copy your API key from project settings
#
# Note: Index name is configured in src/config/ai.config.ts
# Default index name: 'psst-messages'
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
PINECONE_API_KEY=your-pinecone-api-key-here

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google OAuth Client Secret (OPTIONAL)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Used for:
# - Google Calendar integration (backend OAuth token refresh)
#
# NOTE: iOS OAuth clients typically don't require a client secret.
# This is OPTIONAL - only set this if you encounter authentication issues
# with Google Calendar sync.
#
# Where to get it:
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console (https://console.cloud.google.com/)
# 2. Navigate to APIs & Services > Credentials
# 3. If using iOS client credentials, leave this empty
# 4. If you need a web OAuth client, create one and copy the client secret
#
# Leave empty for iOS client (default behavior):
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Firebase Configuration (Auto-configured by Firebase)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are automatically set by Firebase when deploying:
# - FIREBASE_CONFIG (project configuration)
# - GCLOUD_PROJECT (project ID)
#
# You don't need to set these manually for Cloud Functions.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Migration from functions.config()
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DEPRECATION NOTICE: functions.config() is deprecated after March 2026
#
# Old approach (deprecated):
#   firebase functions:config:set openai.api_key="sk-..."
#   firebase functions:config:set pinecone.api_key="..."
#
# New approach (recommended):
#   1. Copy this file to `.env`
#   2. Fill in your API keys
#   3. Update service files to use process.env instead of functions.config()
#   4. Use firebase-functions/params for defineSecret() in production
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
